                            <comment id="12879419" author="adragomir" created="Wed, 16 Jun 2010 17:55:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t know exactly what the logic is, but debugging the Master process yields the following (I looked where I expect the problem is):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. In ChangeTableState::postProcessMeta, there is an iteration on this.unservedRegions, which has size 0. This loop seems to persist the changes to the meta table that say the region is offline&lt;br/&gt;
2. However, this.unservedRegions has size 0, and this.servedRegions has size 1. The table has only 1 region, so I suspect the issue is that somehow, the region should be in unservedRegions, but it isn&apos;t.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13029575" author="stack" created="Thu, 5 May 2011 21:05:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolving cannot reproduce.  This seems to work now.  This issue is also old.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
